reviewText:
{EDIT: I say this IN my review, but I haven't played through this ON STEAM yet, so my hours are not representative of the time it takes to read and re-read this wonderful novel, please keep that in mind.}

Let me start off by saying I love this story. This is to date my favorite Visual Novel out of the many I've played, mostly off steam. I was intrested in the premise of this game a few years before the original enlish fan patch was released, and I picked it up as soon as they were done and read all of it in one go. Since then I've probably re-read all the routes 2 or 3 times and the main route an extra 1 or 2, mostly from streaming it for other people who had yet to experience it. Though I have yet to completly play through it again on steam, I made sure to play enough that I could review it and let people who might be thinking of getting it know: Yes, 100x yes. It's an enjoyable and unique story of cat and mouse, with many intresting characters who grow and flourish as the story continues. I can honestly say I was never bored, however some people who are itching to get to the meat of the story may tire of the into chapter, as it is mostly setting up and getting you introduced to many of the key people in the story, but if you're one of those people, stick to it! It's worth it, and make sure to at least read all the way through the 'true' route, because that's where the real good stuff is at.

TL;DR: The main route is a fantastic game of cat and mouse but it's a bit slow to get going to to that part, which might put some people off, but stick with it and I'm sure you'll love it as much as I do.
